ce:section.ce:para:
SEM was used to examine the morphology of the produced nanofibers with varying Sr.Ber-CQD percentages. All nanofibers have a round form (rod), as seen in the pictures, with smooth surfaces and a morphology devoid of beads (Fig. 5
                           ). Image J software was used to measure the electrospun filaments' diameter, and the average was 191 ± 22 nm. The smallest and biggest diameters of the zero and 10 % nanofibers were 168.05 and 214.66 nm, respectively. This indicated that the diameter of the nanofibers increased somewhat when the mass of the nanofibers and the percentage of Sr.Ber-CQD increased (Fig. 6
                           ).
